data.title: Dannie Heineman Prize for Astrophysics
data.text:
From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia

Recognizes outstanding mid-career work in the field of astrophysics

This article is about the astrophysics prize named after Dannie Heineman. For other prizes likewise named, see Dannie Heineman Prize.

The Dannie Heineman Prize for Astrophysics is jointly awarded each year by the American Astronomical Society and American Institute of Physics for outstanding work in astrophysics.[1] It is funded by the Heineman Foundation in honour of Dannie Heineman.
